#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Apostate, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Apostate.cfg:3
msgid "Apostate"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Apostate, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Apostate.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"The winged monsters known as Apostates were once clergymen totally devote to "
"Light who, for some reason, have refused their beliefs. Corrupted by the Dark"
" Gods, these men have became cruel and bloodthirsty demons who are totally "
"devote to Ba'al."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Apostate.cfg:39
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Heretic.cfg:33
msgid "cursed battleaxe"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Apostate.cfg:52
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Heretic.cfg:46
msgid "fimbulwinter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Archdaemon, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Archdaemon.cfg:3
msgid "Archdaemon"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Archdaemon, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Archdaemon.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"In the Anakes society, an Archdaemon is the governor of an infernal kingdom "
"and have been blessed by the touch of Ba'al the Crimson himself. Archdaemons "
"are masters in the use of the scythe and expert magicians. An Archdaemon "
"leaves his kingdom only to lead a great army in an important campaign."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Archdaemon.cfg:86
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Daemon.cfg:80
msgid "cursed scythe"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Archdaemon.cfg:100
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Daemon.cfg:94
msgid "firestorm"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Cursed, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Cursed.cfg:3
msgid "Cursed"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Cursed, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Cursed.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"The demons known as Cursed are spawned by souls of men killed with cursed "
"weapons by a demon. Cursed are weak and can hardly use swords to defend "
"themselves, so they are the least important soldiers in the Crimson Legion "
"and are usually placed in the first line and used to weaken the enemies."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Daemon, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Daemon.cfg:3
msgid "Daemon"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Daemon, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Daemon.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"Daemons are nobles in the Anakes society and officers of the Crimson Legion. "
"In the demoniacal society, nobility coincides with the favour of the Dark "
"Gods, so the aristocrats are deadlier than common demons. Daemons wield "
"scythes, the traditional weapon of the demoniacal nobility, and they also "
"have magical powers which allow them to use flames against their enemies."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Damned, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Damned.cfg:3
msgid "Damned"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Damned, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Damned.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"A Damned come into the world when a soul is corrupted by the Dark Gods and "
"become totally devote to Ba'al. Damned are the staple of the Crimson Legion "
"and in all these demons flow the power of the Dark Gods, which give them "
"unnatural strength and allow them to summon small fireballs."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Damned.cfg:29
msgid "cursed scimitar"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Dark_Prophet, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Dark_Prophet.cfg:3
msgid "Dark Prophet"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Dark_Prophet, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Dark_Prophet.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"The Dark Gods sometimes choose a demon to impersonate their will, inspire "
"other demons and corrupt men. These Dark Prophets have terrible powers which "
"allow them to drain health with their touch and to work false miracles."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Dark_Prophet.cfg:49
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Hierophant.cfg:44
msgid "dark storm"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Devil, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Devil.cfg:3
msgid "Devil"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Devil, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Devil.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"The strongest and fastest Imps receive heavier armors and deadly swords "
"created with the flames of the hellish kingdoms of the Anakes. These demons, "
"known as Devils, move rapidly on battlefield, attack infantrymen who have "
"broken formation and suddenly retreat when great groups of enemies arrive."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Fiend, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Fiend.cfg:3
msgid "Fiend"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Fiend, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Fiend.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"Fiends are strong and brave demons well-known for their cruelty; they are "
"often instructed to protect the commanders of the Crimson Legion or the Dark "
"Prophets. Fiends are veteran soldiers who wear heavy armors and wield flaming"
" swords."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Heretic, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Heretic.cfg:3
msgid "Heretic"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Heretic, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Heretic.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"During their life as humans, Heretics had been well-known misbelievers who "
"tried to take away people from their traditional beliefs. Heretics serve the "
"Dark Gods with unnatural loyalty and fanaticism, due to the brainwashing they"
" had undergone becoming demons."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Heterodox, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Heterodox.cfg:3
msgid "Heterodox"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Heterodox, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Heterodox.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"Heterodox are demons created with the soul of men who in life had been great "
"misbelievers and have been corrupted by demons. Heterodox are feared for "
"their cruelty, their physical strength and their magical powers, which allow "
"them to use ice spell against their enemies."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Heterodox.cfg:46
msgid "iceball"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Hierophant, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Hierophant.cfg:3
msgid "Hierophant"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Hierophant, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Hierophant.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"Some Initiates who show uncommon charisma and devotion to the Dark Gods "
"become Hierophants of Ba'al. Hierophants are instructed to spread the cult of"
" the Dark Gods and provide souls in order to create new soldiers for the "
"Crimson Legion. A Hierophant doesn't seek for knowledge, so his magical "
"powers aren't as great as the ones of a Spellcaster, but he can heal his "
"allies."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Hierophant.cfg:34
msgid "dark staff"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Imp, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Imp.cfg:3
msgid "Imp"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Imp, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Imp.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"Imps are small winged demons who are used as explorers by the commanders of "
"the Crimson Legion. Imps don't represent a danger for a well-trained soldier,"
" so they are  usually considered sacrificable pawns by their superiors."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Initiate, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Initiate.cfg:3
msgid "Initiate"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Initiate, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Initiate.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"Some demons shows an uncommon propensity to magic and an instinctive "
"comprehension of how to cast spells. These demons receive a special training "
"which allow them to use black magic to fight their enemies or cure their "
"allies. Even though these demons have just begun to explore the secrets of "
"black magic, they can be dangerous foes."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Initiate.cfg:46
msgid "dark burst"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Leech_Dragoon, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Leech_dragoon.cfg:3
msgid "Leech Dragoon"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Leech_Dragoon, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Leech_dragoon.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
" Leech Dragoons are chosen among the best Leech Knights, they undergo a "
"specific training, wear heavy armors and wield flaming swords. Leech Dragoons"
" are well-known for their bravery and their cruelty on the battlefield."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Leech_Knight, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Leech_knight.cfg:3
msgid "Leech Knight"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Leech_Knight, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Leech_knight.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"Demons who manage to ride Brain Drainers achieve the rank of Leech Knight. "
"Brain Drainers are stronger than horses and can wound with their bite, so "
"Leech Knights are deadlier than human knights."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Leech_Rider, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Leech_rider.cfg:3
msgid "Leech Rider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Leech_Rider, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Leech_rider.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"One of the most fearful kind of monster known is the Giant Leech, an enormous"
" worm-like monster that can drain away health from its victims. The Anakes "
"managed to control Giant Leeches and use them as mount. Leech Riders are "
"magically bounded with their mount so the health drained by the Giant Leech "
"heal also the demon."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Massacrer, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Massacrer.cfg:3
msgid "Massacrer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Massacrer, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Massacrer.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"A Slaughterer who had demonstrated uncommon bravery and strength to the Dark "
"Gods become deadlier and more powerful, his body undergo other mutations and "
"he become a perfect fighting machine that can be stopped only by his lord."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Sharp_Eye, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Sharp_Eye.cfg:3
msgid "Sharp Eye"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Sharp_Eye, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Sharp_Eye.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"Some demons show a natural propensity to archery and are more precise and "
"dangerous than common Snipers. These demons use greater and deadlier bows and"
" attack light infantrymen who have broken formation."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Sharp_Eye.cfg:51
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Sniper.cfg:52
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Terrorbow.cfg:56
msgid "dark arrow"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Slaughterer, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Slaughterer.cfg:3
msgid "Slaughterer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Slaughterer, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Slaughterer.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"Some Damned receive great powers by the Dark Gods, they grow bigger and "
"stronger than common demons and their body undergo horrible mutations, but "
"they lose all their magical powers. These fearful warriors are called "
"Slaughterers because they fight with an unnatural bloodlust and kill every "
"enemy who get in their path."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Sniper, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Sniper.cfg:3
msgid "Sniper"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Sniper, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Sniper.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"The Anakes are not keen on using bows, which are considered weapons used by "
"cowards, but some of the physically weaker demons choose to be trained at "
"archery to become a Sniper. Snipers try to avoid melee fight and use poison "
"to weaken their enemies. Snipers have also magical powers that allow them to "
"enchant their darts."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Spellcaster, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Spellcaster.cfg:3
msgid "Spellcaster"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Spellcaster, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Spellcaster.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"Initiates who spent years studying black magic achieve great powers and an "
"higher rank in the Crimson Legion. These powerful mages are known as "
"Spellcasters and are feared because of their mastery of magic and their "
"cruelty on the battlefield. Spellcasters use powerful black magic based on "
"darkness, but they abandon the studies on healing magic, so they cannot cure "
"their allies."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Spellcaster.cfg:30
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Wizard.cfg:33
msgid "cursed staff"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Spellcaster.cfg:44
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Wizard.cfg:46
msgid "dark meteor"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Stormbringer, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Stormbringer.cfg:3
msgid "Stormbringer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Stormbringer, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Stormbringer.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"Some Imps who have demonstrated great loyalty and strength receive magical "
"powers by the Dark Gods, which allow them to create storms and use it to "
"defeat their enemies. These demons are called Stormbringers because of their "
"powers and usually are instructed to break the enemies' formation using "
"bolts."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Terrorbow, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Terrorbow.cfg:3
msgid "Terrorbow"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Terrorbow, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Terrorbow.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"A few demons manage to become masters of archery, but those demons are as "
"deadly as the best elvish archers. The best demoniacal archers are called "
"Terrorbows because of their great bows made up with the bones of their "
"enemies. It's hard to see a Terrorbow on the battlefield, because they hide "
"and shoot at their enemies from a safe place."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Wizard, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Wizard.cfg:3
msgid "Wizard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Wizard, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Wizard.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"Even if they have centuries to study black magic, only a few demon achieve "
"the rank of Wizard in the Crimson Legion, so these extremely powerful mages "
"are almost a legend among the Anakes. Wizards know every secret of black "
"magic and are usually governors of a county or a dukedom or counsellors of  "
"an Arch-daemon."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_outlaws_Brigand, race=human
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\c1-Brigand.cfg:3
msgid "Brigand"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_outlaws_Brigand, race=human
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\c1-Brigand.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Mounted and wielding wicked-looking sickles, brigands left behind the farming"
" life to stalk Wesnoth's lonely backroads in small bands, robbing travelers. "
"They also carry crude crossbows but are not very skilled with them."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\c1-Brigand.cfg:28
msgid "sickle"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Young Ogre
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\d1-Young_Ogre.cfg:7
msgid ""
"When still young, Ogres are sometimes captured and taken into armies to be "
"trained. They cannot manage weapons skillfully, but they compensate for that "
"lack with great strength."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ogre
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\d2-Ogre.cfg:8
msgid ""
"Ogres are giant creatures that usually live alone in the wilderness, "
"remarkably similar to humans in form, though large and misshapen. While they "
"can be easily outrun or outsmarted, their strength is not to be "
"underestimated."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Skeleton
#. [unit_type], id=Dark Adept
#. [unit_type], id=Dark Sorcerer
#. [unit_type], id=Lich
#: .\units\EE_units\undead\a1-Skeleton.cfg:10
#: .\units\EE_units\undead\b1-Dark_Adept.cfg:10
#: .\units\EE_units\undead\b2-Dark_Sorcerer.cfg:10
#: .\units\EE_units\undead\b3-Lich.cfg:11
msgid ""
"This unit is from Extended Era. Its coding and art were done by the Various "
"people who created Extended Era."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Roc, race=monster
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\f1_Roc.cfg:3
msgid "Roc"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Roc, race=monster
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\f1_Roc.cfg:16
msgid ""
"The mighty birds of the desert are large enough to eat horses and cattle. "
"They are not many in number and they do not fly quickly but the simple "
"majesty of them is wondrous to behold. A few particularly brave aristocrats "
"have managed to tame them as mounts but the upkeep of such a creature is "
"elephantine and as such it is very rare to see more than one per city."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Great_Roc, race=monster
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\f2_GreatRoc.cfg:3
msgid "Great Roc"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Great_Roc, race=monster
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\f2_GreatRoc.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Most rocs are enormous by the standards of any bird but in truth most can "
"grow bigger if regularly supplied with food. Their style of hunting is "
"unlikely to allow for such a supply but if the roc is being fed by a wealthy "
"human or has had opportunity to grow fat on the carcasses of battle one might"
" encounter a bird large enough to lift a cow off the ground without "
"difficulty."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_chs_elvish_spirits
#: .\units\EoC_units\elves-wood.cfg:5
msgid "race^Elvish Spirit"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_chs_elvish_spirits
#: .\units\EoC_units\elves-wood.cfg:6
msgid "race+female^Elvish Spirit"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_chs_elvish_spirits
#: .\units\EoC_units\elves-wood.cfg:7
msgid "race^Elvish Spirits"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_chs_elvish_spirits
#: .\units\EoC_units\elves-wood.cfg:8
msgid ""
"Many mighty elven warriors of ancient have died in such a way that their "
"desire of fighting for a last time is not fulfilled. Thus, their souls cannot"
" rest in peace forever, and seek to return to this world for getting their "
"thirst quenched with a last glorious confrontation.\n"
"\n"
"However, they usually cannot do so without help of necromancy. Since elves "
"have always been opposed to allowing necromancy and their practitioners "
"amongst their people, their ancestors have not had the opportunity to return "
"to assist their kind, till now."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_steelhive_Amniote, race=AE_agl_steelhive, gender=female
